                  <interp inst="t18310407-226-crimeloc1214" type="placeName" value="the Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-226-crimeloc1214" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-226-off1211 t18310407-226-crimeloc1214"></join>. On the 23rd of February, about five o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came in, and asked for a pair of boots I went outside the window to get him a boot; I saw him take these shoes, and put them into his pocket - I came in, and he said the boots I showed him were too light, he wanted strong ones; he went out, and I called Stop thief! he was taken without my losing sight of him, and the shoes found in his coat pocket.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that the shoes found on him, he had just taken out of pledge.</p>
               <p>C. BAMFIELD. It is not true - I saw him take them off the shop-board.</p>
